<item>
            <title>[LU-18973] MGC on MGS doesn&apos;t configure any failover nodes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18973</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MGC started on MGS uses always single peer &lt;tt&gt;@lo&lt;/tt&gt; no matter what other services are running on the same node. That leads to situation when MGS is failed over then no services on primary node are able to reach it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solution is to account all &apos;mgsnode&apos; parameters parsed in &lt;tt&gt;lustre_start_mgc()&lt;/tt&gt; from any user of MGC and adding them to MGC import&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
